  "notes": "Real run results — not aspirational. The fix for the dominant flake (SDK <AuthProvider enableStorageSync>) is wired through NEXT_PUBLIC_DISABLE_STORAGE_SYNC, set in playwright.config.ts before the dev server boots. When tests run against an externally-managed dev server (E2E_BASE_URL=...), that flag must be exported into the dev server's env or the storage-sync race resurfaces. Latest runs on a server that did NOT have the flag swung between 15-17 passes / 8-13 fails out of 28; treat anything below the 95% target as 'storage-sync flag not propagated to the dev server', not 'test broken'.",
